{
  "texts": [
    ":(0123456789) Scientific Reports | (2024) 14:1589 | https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-024-51258-6 www.nature.com/scientificreports/ CIFAR-100 dataset The CIFAR-100 dataset is a classic dataset widely used for computer vision tasks.",
    "It is an extended version of the CIFAR-10 dataset, consisting of 100 different fine-grained categories.",
    "Each category has 600 images, resulting in a total of 60,000 images.",
    "These categories cover a wide range of objects, animals, and everyday items such as chairs, tables, flowers, insects, and more.",
    "Similar to CIFAR-10, each image in CIFAR-100 has a size of 32 × 32 pixels and consists of RGB channels."
  ]
}